President Xi Jinping on Friday called for efforts to break new ground in the work concerning veterans affairs. Xi, also general secretary of the Communist Party of China Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military Commission, made the remarks while meeting with representatives who are in Beijing to attend a national conference on the work of veterans affairs. 
